trend_summary: Across the series, the peninsula keeps its residential layout but experiences steady infill: new cul-de-sacs, an expanded shopping plaza and denser tree canopy. Green buffers along the river grow wider, yet no major sprawl beyond the existing footprint occurs. Net result is a stable, medium-density suburban setting with incremental renewal.
notable_changes: Central shopping centre enlarged; several new white-roof blocks appear after the midpoint.
Vacant lots in southwest and southeast converted to residential cul-de-sacs.
Riparian vegetation widens, especially along the northeast shoreline, indicating restoration.
New connector road and small loop added on western edge, tightening street mesh.
Southern sports field reconfigured, adding mixed recreation and greener coverage.
